<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.67.52055>
    bibo:endPage "80" ;
    bibo:journal "MycoKeys" ;
    bibo:startPage "55" ;
    bibo:volume "67" ;
    dc:creator "Valle, Laia Guardia; Stoianova, Desislava" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "First record of Harpellales, Orphellales (Kickxellomycotina) and Amoebidiales (Mesomycetozoea) from Bulgaria, including a new species of Glotzia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.67.52055.figures11-16> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.67.52055.figures11-16>
    dc:description "Figures 11 - 16. Various species of Harpellales. 11 - 13 Graminella microspora from Baetidae nymphs: 11 thallus overview, with inflated basal cell structures from which propagules arise or are extruded (note: one empty basal cell which has extruded its cellular content, arrow); young zygospores can also be observed (arrowhead) 12 a cluster of basal cells 13 fertile branch with a long series of minute trichospores; 14, 15 Harpella melusinae from Simuliidae larvae: 14 generative cells and allantoids or curved trichospores 15 basal cell and small conic holdfast 16 Legeriomyces ramosus from Baetidae nymphs, zygospores and zygosporophores. Scale bars: 25 μm in all figures." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/414541" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

